This paper discusses the importance of semantics-based tool generation in programming language design, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the potential for incorporating substantial amounts of semantic knowledge into language design assistants, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of semantics in programming languages can also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
